      • insertChild

        protected void insertChild(TypeSystemNode newChild)
                    throws org.jacorb.ir.gui.typesystem.IllegalChildException
        Adds a new child to a node. Only called by TypeSystem.insertChild(...). Here it doesn't do anything except throw an exception, if newChild is not permitted, hence it must be overridden by subclasses, e.g. to call the corresponding method on IR. Throws IllegalChildException for illegal child type.
        Parameters:
        newChild - TypeSystemNode
        Throws:
        org.jacorb.ir.gui.typesystem.IllegalChildException
